  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> I have a mage who's 27, and I was killing junk in Seru and happened to look at my defense skill, and it was 12. lol Is this normal for mages? I was never pl'd and soloed the whole way cept for one time on dervs in nro =P.<br>
<br>
Anyone have any ideas on a safe way to raise this? I'd do the duel a pet class pc and let the pet hit me, but all my friend are rangers and druids and such hehe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usawzallz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sawzallz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#333333>(8/17/02 1:29:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> <br>
overnuke when in grps and you will eventually get the skill up =) if you try this I suggest making a hotkey like &quot;GET IT OFF ME!!!&quot; <p>
<a target="new" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234133> Ghetto_and_proud</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umissingruby.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MissingRuby</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333333>(8/17/02 8:11:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> At skill 12 I would put some trainingpoints into my defense before even thinking about tanking a few hits. Always remember to let your group know that you are deliberately tanking and don't get too low on HPs. <p><img src="http://www.ravnsborg.esenet.dk/sig.jpg">
<BR> 
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76695"</A> 
<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=300011"</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uturzem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turzem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(8/17/02 11:25:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> [qutoe]At skill 12 I would put some trainingpoints into my defense before even thinking about tanking a few hits.[/quote]<br>
<br>
You can't train Defense, FYI.<br>
<br>
Find another pet class and have the pet duel you, you get skillups like that. <p><b><center><font size="2" face="perpetua"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=302063">Turzem Setanta</a> -- <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">Conjurer</a>
<br><a href="mailto:yolora@attbi.com">E-Mail</a></font></center></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufizzden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fizzden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(8/18/02 1:01:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> here is what i did.. tank to 50% health and back off and you will get some skill points up.. i finally got mine maxxed out at 52.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflambodius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flambodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(8/18/02 3:36:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> What's the skill cap for defense? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufarmatyr1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>farmatyr1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#333333>(8/18/02 6:31:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> 145 is the cap. not sure if it's higher post 50.<br>
<br>
cap is 75 for dodge.<br>
<br>
Anyway, to the original poster, I would strongly recommend trying to max it now. At 27, the mobs don't hit that hard, bind wound still heals you relatively fast, and decent buffs will make a massive difference in your tanking ability. My magician is 40 right now, with around 122 defense. I can stand up to mobs and take a few hits without instantly dying, so I can get those last few points. If I was at 20 defense, though, mobs would beat me down so fast it would be very painful to try to get my skill up without using the pet trick. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xalmat>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#333333>(8/18/02 7:00:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> Defense just naturally goes up for me. Level 55 now, defense is somewhere in the 120s. Sure, every bit of AC helps, but chances are that if you get beat on you're dead until something taunts the mob off or you outrun it. This is especially true in your 40s and 50s where many mobs are hitting well into the 100s (some even into the 200s). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzacatac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1090<br> <font color=#333333>(8/19/02 4:57:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> You very much want to work on that skill.  Having a level 50 mob miss you a few times is a good thing at higher levels.  Best way is to do some soloing vs. blue or lt. blue mobs and jump into the fight.  Mob will hit you instead of pet since you are PC.  Get a weapon and some offense skill while you are at it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Get them maxed out at an early level, it will greatly help you later.  Both of these should be capped someday.<br>
<br>
Defense 145<br>
Dodge 75<br>
